ent in 2028, he may for the first time accept fundraising dollars, NBC News has learned</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2028-election/billionaire-illinois-gov-jb-pritzker-not-fully-self-finance-2028-run-rcna343122</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2028-election/billionaire-illinois-gov-jb-pritzker-not-fully-self-finance-2028-run-rcna343122</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260430-Pritzker-vsb-1702-6609fa.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Angelina Katsanis</media:credit><media:text type="plain">J.B. Pritzker</media:text><media:description type="plain">Illinois Gov. J.B. Pritzker speaks at the National Action Network Convention in New York, on April 9.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260430-Pritzker-vsb-1702-6609fa.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 19:59:44 GMT</pubDate><title>Billionaire Illinois Gov. JB Pritzker explores something new in a 2028 run: Raising money</title><updateDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 21:36:59 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Henry J. Gomez</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Sat, 02 May 2026 00:00:34 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>President Donald Trump moved Friday to thin the Republican field running for Senate in Kentucky, endorsing Rep.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/trump-endorses-rep-andy-barr-kentucky-senate-primary-rcna343158</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/trump-endorses-rep-andy-barr-kentucky-senate-primary-rcna343158</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-Senate--candidate-Andy-Barr-vsb-1930-198010.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Tom Williams</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Rep. Andy Barr</media:text><media:description type="plain">Rep. Andy Barr, R-Ky., at the Capitol Hill Club, in March.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-Senate--candidate-Andy-Barr-vsb-1930-198010.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Sat, 02 May 2026 00:00:34 GMT</pubDate><title>Trump endorses Rep. Andy Barr in Kentucky Senate primary</title><updateDate>Sat, 02 May 2026 00:00:34 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Alexandra Marquez</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Monica Alba</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Bridget Bowman</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Fri, 01 May 2026 13:58:22 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Former President Joe Biden on Friday backed former Atlanta mayor Keisha Lance Bottoms&#39; campaign for governor in Georgia, his first endorsement since leaving office last year.&#34;I&#39;ve known her for a long time, and she&#39;s something special,&#34; Biden said in a video backing the former mayor, who served as a senior adviser in the Biden administration</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/biden-endorses-keisha-lance-bottoms-georgia-governor-rcna343057</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/biden-endorses-keisha-lance-bottoms-georgia-governor-rcna343057</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-Keisha-Lance-Bottoms-Biden-ch-0918-d86973.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="800" width="1200"><media:credit>Getty Images</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A split composite of Joe Biden and Keisha Lance Bottoms.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Former President Joe Biden said Keisha Lance Bottoms is &#34;ready&#34; to be governor of Georgia.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-Keisha-Lance-Bottoms-Biden-ch-0918-d86973.jpg" height="800" width="1200"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 13:58:22 GMT</pubDate><title>Biden backs Keisha Lance Bottoms for Georgia governor in his first endorsement since leaving office</title><updateDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 13:58:22 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Jane C. Timm </dc:creator><dc:contributor>Rebecca Shabad</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Adam Edelman</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Fri, 01 May 2026 19:09:48 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Alabama Gov. Kay Ivey called legislators into a special session Friday and asked them to reschedule the state&#39;s midterm primaries, in hopes that pushing those elections back will give them time to re-install congressional maps that had been blocked in court before a landmark Supreme Court ruling changed the landscape around race and redistricting this week</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/alabama-governor-calls-special-session-move-primaries-redistricting-ge-rcna343125</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/alabama-governor-calls-special-session-move-primaries-redistricting-ge-rcna343125</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-Kay-Ivey-gk-06cf66.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1668" width="2500"><media:credit>Vasha Hunt</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Kay Ivey</media:text><media:description type="plain">Alabama Gov. Kay Ivey in 2023, in Troy, Ala.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-Brian-Kemp-gk-57ae10.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Brynn Anderson</media:credit><media:text type="plain">State of the State Georgia</media:text><media:description type="plain">Alabama Gov. Kay Ivey in 2023, in Troy, Ala.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260501-Kay-Ivey-gk-06cf66.jpg" height="1668" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 19:09:48 GMT</pubDate><title>Alabama governor calls special session to move primaries for redistricting, while Georgia passes</title><updateDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 23:54:10 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Jonathan Allen</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Fri, 01 May 2026 11:00:41 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Sen. Elizabeth Warren, D-Mass., plans to campaign for Iowa Senate candidate Zach Wahls this month, adding firepower to a raging battle between progressive outsider candidates and the Democratic Party establishment</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/elizabeth-warren-campaign-iowa-progressive-senate-candidate-rcna342989</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2026-election/elizabeth-warren-campaign-iowa-progressive-senate-candidate-rcna342989</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260430-wahls-warren-split-ww-1652-3d426c.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="800" width="1200"><media:credit>Getty Images file</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Sen. Elizabeth Warren, D-Mass.; Iowa Senate candidate Zach Wahls</media:text><media:description type="plain">Sen. Elizabeth Warren, D-Mass., and Iowa state Sen. Zach Walls.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260430-wahls-warren-split-ww-1652-3d426c.jpg" height="800" width="1200"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 11:00:41 GMT</pubDate><title>Elizabeth Warren to campaign in Iowa for progressive Senate candidate</tit